Text.Value: It is no coup - it is the opportunity of our entire lives!
In the name of the Spider Queen - we fly!
The time for planning is over! Follow me, brothers - into her hairy embrace!
Murmath? Is that the guy who keeps telling everyone about his useless, hideous spiders?
Hey! Knock it off, the lot of you!
*You sense very little from the shifting trio.*
*These spiders are loyal to the local duergar. In the event of a fight, they will join the fray against you - with slavering enthusiasm.*
We need no 'Order' - Father Murmath is the way!
All three! Follow me, brothers - we will find our due among the Spider Queen's dedicants. We deserve as much!
This and so much more. In Lolth's hairy embrace, all is possible.
I think your sister is right - among the Spider Queen's worshippers, you'll reach your true potential.
HAHA! Yes! Now, brothers - our new dawn awaits!
What care we for his business here? He keeps us small. Keeps us contained. We should be with the Spider Queen - revered, adored!
We owe Father Murmath all we are - and we will never betray him!
Fie! Xanta - even the Spider Queen's faithful wants no part in your game!
We need no 'Lolth' - no spider queen! Father Murmath is the head of clan Lur. He hatched us, raised us, feeds us!
You should know that spiders are revered among Lolth's faithful. Harming one of your kind is a capital crime.
I'd rather not get involved in your little coup.
But it goes beyond logic. Do not you feel it, brothers? The pull for something more? Do you not see it, friend visitor? Their unfulfilled potential?
But - but the Spider Queen! Lolth! Our due!
*You don't sense much unfulfilled potential, but one thing is certain: this crew won't hesitate to sink their fangs into your belly if their duergar master gives the word.*
I suppose the Order of the Soul Spiders would have room for you among their ranks.
Being bound to serve Murmath spits in the face of natural order. It limits you.
Why be bound to Murmath when you could be Lolth's avenging justiciars?
Your duty is to each other, not Murmath. Embrace that, and power unlimited will be yours.
You owe nothing to Murmath. Break your bonds, free yourselves. Become unstoppable.
Turning on your head-of-clan, are you? I'm sure that'll end well.
He... he might've! He doesn't know our true potential - our true splendour! Only Lolth knows that.
The Spider Queen doesn't suffer hesitation. I fear for anyone who resists her call.
Try to discern the nature of their chatter.
We will not betray Father Murmath. We will never leave him!
You! Please - explain to my brothers - we must be among our own kind!
Among the Spider Queen's followers, you'd be revered as her physical manifestation. Honoured. Exalted.
*They appear to be in conflict - the larger spider versus the other three.*
Fools! Don't you see - the time of Murmath has passed! The Spider Queen awaits us!
You see? Father Murmath's time has passed. Come, brothers - follow me into Lolth's hairy embrace!
Recall your learnings about the Spider Queen, Lolth.
Stand back and see how things play out.
We do not turn on Father Murmath. But we do outgrow him. The fate of clan Lur lies with the Spider Queen!
I speak true, brothers! You know it in your hearts! You know it in your very souls!
I don't care where you go, but it's time for all of you to leave.
Spiders for the Spider Queen. Seems logical.
I've heard the very same! Come, brothers - follow me into her hairy embrace!
Your sister speaks true. The Spider Queen would welcome you with great enthusiasm.
*You've read that harming spiders is illegal among Lolth's faithful - and often punishable by death.*
You see?! Such disrespect! Such disdain! And does Father Murmath raise a whisper in our defence? With the Spider Queen's protection, we would never suffer such indignity again!
*These spiders aren't wild - they've been raised by local duergar and are fiercely loyal to them.*
Father Murmath is our past - Lolth is our future!
He is all he is and all he is not!

Synopsis:
In this dialogue, Lur Xanta is trying to convince the other 3 to leave with her to join the cult of Lolth.
Player can help her convince them, or fail to do so and they will attack Lur Xanta for being disloyal.

This dialogue has 2 outcomes:

AGGRO: Lur Jox (or another spider) attacks Lur Xanta, killing her in one shot. (via gameplay - not cine)
PEACEFUL: Lur Xanta convinces the other 3 to follow her into the Underdark-- they are leaving to somewhere new.

Lur Xanta is fantatical and somewhat learned. The other 3 are a bit more simple.
